\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid10836955 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af46\afs26 \ltrch\fcs0 \f46\fs26\kerning0\insrsid11555524 \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 
The ARM Architecture Reference Manual for ARMv8-A is the single most important document for this project. Read the chapters on exception levels, the memory management unit, Stage 2 translation, the GIC architecture, the SMMU, and the architectural timer i
\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 n particular.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 The AOSP source tree is its own form of reading. Build it, modify it, understand its structure. The hardware abstraction layer interfaces and the device configuration system are where AETHER's customization happens.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 
The Linux kernel source for the ARM64 architecture, particularly the KVM subsystem, provides a reference implementation of every concept AETHER implements. KVM is not what AETHER is, but KVM solves many of the same problems AETHER must solve, and its sour
\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 ce is the most readable specification of the solutions.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 
The Xen Project documentation, particularly for Xen on ARM, describes a Type-1 hypervisor architecture closer to AETHER's than KVM's. Xen's design choices are not all appropriate for AETHER, but the rationale Xen documents for each choice is invaluable.

\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 The microG project documentation describes the API surface microG implements and the gaps relative to genuine Google Play Services.
\par 
